5 I live in chicago and today, after a night of liver destruction...I was forced to order chinese food.  I have lived here for a year and have not found THE CHINESE place.  Mr. Chao's Asian Bistro has ruined me for life.   By far the best chinese food I have ever had in all of my 34 years. I love it so much that I had it as my last meal before I relocated to Chicago.    The veggies are crisp and fresh and the flavors POW, BANG,ZOOM in your mouth.    I should also mention that it is a chinese food restaurant that you actually want to eat in and not just pick up or get delivery.  Great atmosphere, i use to take friends there all the time.  I have a friend here in Chicago that visited me while I lived there and she actually just said to me the other day " i wish i had some mr chaos" .  I miss you Mr Chaos.
